A federal prosecutor in the office of the Attorney General And Minister of Justice, Barrister Labaran Shuaibu Magaji, has donated 10,000 copies of science textbooks to secondary school students in Toto Local Government Council of Nasarawa State. Magaji, while performing the flag-off of the distribution in Toto on Saturday, said the textbooks were for both senior and junior secondary school students in the LGA. He said the textbooks would encourage students to study science. The principal of Government Secondary School (GSS) Toto, Malam Usman Ibrahim, commended Barr Magaji for donating the textbooks.